The paper deals with decentralized estimation in wireless sensor networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of multiple-bit quantization for digital transmission suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the development of optimal and suboptimal estimators involves machine learning (cs.LG).
